# Record documents — print, PDF, and send

Every record page that offers **print**, **PDF**, or **send/issue** document actions must use the shared pattern below.

## UI pattern (mandatory)

| Requirement | Implementation |
|-------------|----------------|
| Placement | Bottom of the record tab or detail view — **after** main content, before tasks footer if present |
| Component | `RecordDocumentsSection` from `web/src/components/record-documents-section.tsx` |
| Styling | Subtle — small uppercase "Documents" label, ghost buttons; **no** loud primary/pink header buttons |
| Instructions | Link **How to print and send** to the help article section — **no** inline step lists or delivery panels |
| Send handoff | `mailtoUrl` + `Open email draft` on the section only after issue/send succeeds |

```tsx
<RecordDocumentsSection
  entityType="invoice"
  entityId={record.id}
  refreshKey={historyRefresh}
  error={printError || sendError}
  message={printMessage || sendMessage}
  mailtoUrl={handoff?.mailtoUrl}
  mailtoReady={issued}
  extras={/* optional template picker, period filter */}
  actions={[
    { processId: DOCUMENT_PRINT_PROCESSES.printInvoice, label: "Print", onClick: handlePrint },
    { processId: DOCUMENT_PRINT_PROCESSES.printInvoice, label: "PDF", onClick: handlePdf, busy: pdfBusy },
    { processId: DOCUMENT_PRINT_PROCESSES.sendInvoice, label: "Issue", onClick: handleIssue, variant: "primary" },
  ]}
/>
```

Bump `historyRefresh` after every successful print, PDF, or send so **Saved files** and **Print log** reload.

## Audit and registry (mandatory)

| Action | Call |
|--------|------|
| Print / PDF that registers HTML | `registerDocumentWithAudit()` from `web/src/lib/document-print-audit.ts` |
| Print-only (popup blocked) | `auditDocumentProcess({ outcome: "failed", failureReason: "Print window blocked" })` |
| PDF via `downloadDocumentPdf` | `auditDocumentProcess({ detail: "PDF download" })` after success |
| Send/issue API | `auditDocumentProcess()` on success with registry document no |

Do **not** call raw `registerGeneratedDocument` without process audit on record pages.

## Help links

Map process ids in `web/src/lib/record-document-help.ts`. Add new print/send processes there when introduced.

## Permissions

Document actions still require `canProcess(processId)` (via `canRunProcess` — tab write + process grant). Hide the whole section when the user has no document actions.

## Handoff checklist

- [ ] Uses `RecordDocumentsSection` at bottom of record view
- [ ] No duplicate print buttons in `AppShell` actions or loud inline instruction blocks
- [ ] Help link resolves (`record-document-help.ts` + help article section)
- [ ] Saved files list opens stored documents via `/api/documents/view`
- [ ] Print log shows who printed/sent and when
- [ ] Help + TEST/UAT docs updated per `docs-and-testing.mdc`
